features: Mini size, Major Power: Introducing our mini potent yet gentle cleansing spray containing 0.015% hypochlorous acid (HOCL). This magical molecule harnesses natural cleansing properties, bidding farewell to angry skin. Experience the soothing and revitalizing effects of this powerful formula, making it your ultimate go-to for daily skincare.

Effortless Hygiene, Day-Long Revitalization: Embrace the ease of incorporating HOCL into your everyday skincare regimen. Crafted for continuous use, this gentle yet powerful spray seamlessly fits into your day, whether you're at home, in the gym, or on the move. Maintain a consistently fresh and clean feel for your skin!

Minimal Ingredients, Maximized Results: Embracing the potency of natural elements, our formula relies on the remarkable HOCL naturally present in our white blood cells. Our facial spray is composed solely of water, salt, and 0.015% hypochlorous acid, delivering an entirely natural solution to meet your skincare requirements.

Gentle Care for Delicate Skin: HOCL proves to be an all-encompassing solution, ensuring safety for even the most sensitive skin. Safe to use on hormonal acne, wounds, back acne, piercing aftercare, redness, itch, active breakouts, styes, eyelid irritation, and beyond.

Excellence and Openness: Distinguishing itself from other HOCL alternatives, Honeydew Labs presents a spray meticulously crafted for the utmost sensitivity in facial care. With transparent expiration dates for clarity and assurance, it comes in a recyclable opaque PET bottle to shield against light degradation. The non-leaky mist applicator guarantees the durability and efficacy of your hypochlorous acid.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 12, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Super simple addition to routine that really helped
reviews.reviewText: I've got fairly oily, sensitive skin and often get breakouts, but haven't had any since I started using it a couple of months ago! It was a minimal change to my morning and evening routine, but seems help reduce breakouts.I also like that's it's unscented and doesn't have any unnecessary ingredients. You know exactly what you're getting, and also at a really affordable price, especially compared to other beauty products.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 27, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Loving the spray
reviews.reviewText: Nice dupe for tower 28 SOS spray - so many benefits to hypochlorous acid and I like how there’s clear expiration dates on the box!!! I use it also as hand sanitizer sometimes due to the antibacterial aspect!!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 23, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Refreshing and hydrating, but not sure I've seen much difference with blemishes
reviews.reviewText: This is an interesting one, because I like using this spray, but I'm not sure I'm seeing the results I expected. I'm a middle aged woman who gets a few blemishes a day, especially when using beauty products. The promise of a non-irritating option to control this sounded amazing. It's the first time I've used a hypochlorous acid spray, and I like using it. It's refreshing, coolong, and feels nice in general. I do wish it was a finer mist, but it gives good coverage as is. But I have not noticed a significant difference in how many blemishes I get. It does help to calm things down a bit, especially when using it at night, but I guess I was hoping for a miracle that would end blemishes for me and that's certainly not what I got using this product. I do notice a difference on days when I don't use it, thiugh, so I still use it regularly. I had also read this type of product could be good for eczema, and saw no difference using it for that on the few times I tried.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 13, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great for facial cleansing!
reviews.reviewText: I've been using hypochlorous acid often on the days I wear masks all day outside. I used Briotech before, but decided to switch it up and try the Honeydew Labs bottle. So far I like the texture of the more, and the finish on my face feels better as well! Highly recommended.

reviews.reviewText: I have dry skin especially on my eyelids but this spray really helps soothe the redness and itchiness. I keep it in my workout bag and spray my face afterwards. My sensitive skin really appreciates that it’s hypoallergenic

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 8, 2024
Reviewed in the United States on January 2, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Great dupe for Tower28 SOS Spray
reviews.reviewText: I fell in love with Tower28's SOS Rescue spray earlier last year, when I realized I had bene overpaying for what was essentially diluted hypocholorous acid spray. This spray from Honeydew Labs is a fraction of the price at $16.95 (at time of writing) and provides a 0.015% concentration of HOCL, which is the same concentration as the Tower28 spray. The mist nozzle sadly does not dispense a fine mist as I would personally like, but that is easily fixable by decanting the spray into another bottle of my own choosing.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 21, 2023
reviews.reviewText: love how soothing and effective the spray is! definitely including this in my daily skincare routine :)

I don't use this product often (I keep forgetting. I don't really have a skincare "routine"), but when I do use it, I find it pleasant.It is refreshing, seems to help my skin (face feels smoother after use).I remember it stinging a bit the first time, but since then, it's quite gentle and refreshing. 5/5

This product is easy to use. Just spray on after washing your face. You can even spray on eyelids. It is completely non-toxic which is great. I had a few small pimples on the sides of my neck, and after a few sprays over a few days they dried up. I don't think it is supposed to moisturize, so you need to use a moisturizer after spraying with HOCL.

reviews.reviewTitle: Refreshing spray, smells nice like a swimming pool
reviews.reviewText: Upon receiving this spray I was pleased to see it was packaged well and was as advertised and for the price it isn’t too bad, I made it last about 25 days using it once at night and in the morning. I would get the bigger size if I end up getting it again.The spray is nice, smells almost like a swimming pool but not as strong but I actually like it.I find that it has a dry affect that tightens up the face a little and I’ve had some bad acne lately so I was going to see if this would help and so far it didn’t do anything crazy for that unfortunately but I don’t think that’s what this is fully intended for anyway.I must say though it’s definitely refreshing to spray on after a shower, smells good and my face does feel clean and a little better, just not the big difference I was hoping for.Price isn’t too bad though at all, it’s refreshing, smells good and I honestly will probably try and get some again in the future because I have oily skin and I found it dried my face up more decreasing the oily forehead I get often.

Love the convenience of a spray product. I'm not much of a morning skincare person but this makes it so easy to spray quickly before going to work in the morning. No sensitivity and nonirritating, helps my breakouts go away faster as well!

Pros:- Doesn't react negatively to my sensitive skin- Seems to help a little to remove unwanted oil- It's a really big bottle and has a strong sprayCons:- It doesn't have a super noticeable reaction, I prefer my regular witch hazel toner- It smells like pool after I spray my face with this productVerdict:It's not a bad product, but I don't think I'll continue using it. It doesn't react negatively to my sensitive skin, but it does dry out my skin a little, so I don't know if I'll continue with this product. The best results I found was applying this at night and my witch hazel toner in the morning.
